HOUSE BILL 1080
Q3 6lr3448
By: Delegate Solomon
Introduced and read first time: February 10, 2026
Assigned to: Ways and Means
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Income Tax – Addition Modifications – Excluded Opportunity Fund Gains,
3 Foreign–Derived Deduction Eligible Income, and Interest
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting the Governor from nominating a census tract for
5 designation as a qualified opportunity zone; providing an addition modification
6 under the Maryland income tax for the capital gains from certain qualified
7 opportunity funds; providing an addition modification under the Maryland corporate
8 income tax for certain foreign–derived deduction eligible income and the amount of
9 interest paid on loans that secure certain rural property; and generally relating to
10 the effect of amendments to the Internal Revenue Code on the Maryland income tax.
11 BY adding to
12 Article – State Government
13 Section 3–309
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
16 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
17 Article – Tax – General
18 Section 10–204(a) and 10–305(a)
19 Annotated Code of Maryland
20 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
21 BY adding to
22 Article – Tax – General
23 Section 10–204(m) and 10–305(e) and (f)
24 Annotated Code of Maryland
25 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
